                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I personally never used charm much, so I'm not especially bugged by it either.  Perhaps that's because I lacked the AAs/gear/support group to use it properly, or maybe I was just risk-averse all along.  But I do recognize this as a huge nerf.  I find it impossible to believe that the class was balanced before the nerf and is still balanced after the nerf.
<br />

<br />
I'm one of the many folks whose characters were deleted by OOW bugs, so I haven't actually gotten to play this week.  Leaving the bugs in instead of having lots of emergency patches isn't really much of an improvement over previous expansions.  This has given me time to consider the same list as Menlar:
<br />

<br />
No upgrade to WoM
<br />
No upgrade to tashan line
<br />
No upgrade to debuffs (slow/cripple)
<br />
A REDUCED upgrade to self shield when comparing to other int caster upgrades.
<br />
No Magic resistance upgrade
<br />
Stun and nuke upgrades on a shared timer system making them negligable upgrades, at best.
<br />
NO aggro reducer upgrade
<br />
No new illusions/faction modifiers
<br />
No advanced dire charm aa
<br />

<br />
... although there is actually a Cripple upgrade at level 66.
<br />

<br />
On balance, I don't think the days when 'enchantering was about mez' are being preserved any more than charm is.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
